# Inventory — oculus-spider-page-enhancements

## Brief Summary

Six enhancements to the Spider page (`/pages/spider/`):

1. **Rig Templates table** — replace raw JSON block display with tabular format + graphical detail view on row click
2. **Rig List columns** — add writ title, reorder to: Status, Writ Title, Engines, Rig Id, Writ Id, Created
3. **Rig Detail writ details** — show writ title + body spec at top of detail view
4. **Engine elapsed time** — show friendly elapsed duration for completed engines
5. **Quick engine session log** — resizable textarea with message log; live indicator for running sessions
6. **Quick engine costs** — show token/cost summary for completed quick engines

---

## Files That Will Be Changed

### Primary (certain changes)

| File | Nature of change |
|------|-----------------|
| `packages/plugins/spider/src/static/spider.js` | MAJOR — all six features land here |
| `packages/plugins/spider/src/static/index.html` | MODERATE — table headers, new DOM nodes |
| `packages/plugins/spider/src/static/spider.css` | MODERATE — new component styles |
| `packages/plugins/spider/src/oculus-routes.ts` | MODERATE — expand `/api/spider/config`, add routes |

### Probable (if SpiderApi extension chosen)

| File | Nature of change |
|------|-----------------|
| `packages/plugins/spider/src/types.ts` | Add `RigTemplateInfo` type, add `listRigTemplates()` to SpiderApi |
| `packages/plugins/spider/src/spider.ts` | Implement `listRigTemplates()` on the api object |
| `packages/plugins/spider/src/index.ts` | Re-export `RigTemplateInfo` if type is new |

### Adjacent (referenced but not changed)

- `packages/plugins/oculus/src/types.ts` — RouteContribution, OculusKit (shape only)
- `packages/plugins/oculus/src/static/style.css` — shared CSS vars consumed by spider.css
- `packages/plugins/clerk/src/types.ts` — WritDoc (read only)
- `packages/plugins/animator/src/types.ts` — SessionDoc, TranscriptDoc, TokenUsage (read only)
- `packages/plugins/fabricator/src/fabricator.ts` — EngineDesignInfo (already used)

### Test Files

- `packages/plugins/spider/src/spider-oculus.test.ts` — tests for `/api/spider/config` route; will need updates for new/changed route shape
- `packages/plugins/spider/src/spider.test.ts` — existing spider tests; unaffected unless SpiderApi changes
- `packages/plugins/oculus/src/oculus.test.ts` — oculus infrastructure; unaffected

---

## Current Types (exact signatures from source)

### `RigDoc` — `packages/plugins/spider/src/types.ts:83`
```typescript
export interface RigDoc {
  [key: string]: unknown;
  id: string;
  writId: string;
  status: RigStatus;
  engines: EngineInstance[];
  createdAt: string;
  resolutionEngineId?: string;
}
```

### `EngineInstance` — `packages/plugins/spider/src/types.ts:47`
```typescript
export interface EngineInstance {
  id: string;
  designId: string;
  status: EngineStatus;
  upstream: string[];
  givensSpec: Record<string, unknown>;
  yields?: unknown;
  error?: string;
  sessionId?: string;
  startedAt?: string;
  completedAt?: string;
  block?: BlockRecord;
}
```
`EngineStatus = 'pending' | 'running' | 'completed' | 'failed' | 'cancelled' | 'blocked'`

### `RigTemplate` / `RigTemplateEngine` — `packages/plugins/spider/src/types.ts:119`
```typescript
export interface RigTemplateEngine {
  id: string;
  designId: string;
  upstream?: string[];
  givens?: Record<string, unknown>;
}
export interface RigTemplate {
  engines: RigTemplateEngine[];
  resolutionEngine?: string;
}
```

### `SpiderConfig` — `packages/plugins/spider/src/types.ts:279`
```typescript
export interface SpiderConfig {
  pollIntervalMs?: number;
  buildCommand?: string;
  testCommand?: string;
  rigTemplates?: Record<string, RigTemplate>;
  rigTemplateMappings?: Record<string, string>;
  variables?: Record<string, unknown>;
}
```

### `SpiderApi` — `packages/plugins/spider/src/types.ts:233`
```typescript
export interface SpiderApi {
  crawl(): Promise<CrawlResult | null>;
  show(id: string): Promise<RigDoc>;
  list(filters?: RigFilters): Promise<RigDoc[]>;
  forWrit(writId: string): Promise<RigDoc | null>;
  resume(rigId: string, engineId: string): Promise<void>;
  getBlockType(id: string): BlockType | undefined;
  listBlockTypes(): BlockTypeInfo[];
}
```
(No existing method for listing rig templates from the full registry.)

### `WritDoc` — `packages/plugins/clerk/src/types.ts:27`
```typescript
