## RigTemplateRegistry (spider.ts internal class)

```
templates:          Map<string, RigTemplate>   — all templates (config + kit-qualified names)
configMappings:     Map<string, string>         — guild.json writ-type → template-name
kitMappings:        Map<string, string>         — kit writ-type → template-name
configTemplateNames:Set<string>                 — unqualified names of config-declared templates
```

Config templates: stored under their unqualified name (e.g. `"default"`).
Kit templates: stored under qualified name `"pluginId.templateName"`.

Provenance recovery: a template whose name is in `configTemplateNames` came from guild.json; all others are kit-contributed (plugin ID is the prefix before the first `.`).

To expose full registry externally, a new `listRigTemplates()` method is needed on SpiderApi.

