## Writ Title Data Path

`RigDoc` has `writId` but no `writTitle`. To show writ title in the rig list/detail:

**Option A — frontend per-row fetch:** Call `GET /api/writ/show?id={writId}` for each row. Auto-route exists (from `writ-show` tool, `clerk:read`). N=100 max; usable but chatty.

**Option B — frontend bulk fetch:** Call `GET /api/writ/list?limit=...` once, build id→title map. Risk: writ list and rig list may not align without pagination care.

**Option C — new backend join route:** `GET /api/spider/rigs` in `oculus-routes.ts` that fetches all rigs and then looks up each writ from `stacks.readBook<WritDoc>('clerk', 'writs')`. Spider internally already opens this book (`writsBook`). Clean, single fetch from frontend. Requires adding `ClerkApi` import to `oculus-routes.ts`.

