## Key Observations

1. **Template provenance recovery:** Config templates have unqualified names (e.g. `"default"`); kit templates have `"pluginId.templateName"` qualified names. When listing all templates from the registry, source can be inferred from name structure. The `configTemplateNames` set in the registry makes this explicit.

2. **Writ type mapping display:** The brief says rig template table should show "writ type mappings". For the table to show which writ types map to each template, both `configMappings` and `kitMappings` need to be exposed. This information is also private to the registry class.

3. **Rig list currently uses writId as filter text** (`id="writ-filter"`, placeholder "Filter by writ ID..."). With the new Writ Title column, consider whether to also allow filtering by title — but this is outside the brief scope.

4. **Session detail caching:** When `showEngineDetail(engine)` is called, if the engine has a `sessionId`, the session data (cost/log) should be fetched lazily. The current code doesn't fetch anything external. A `fetchSession(sessionId)` helper will be needed.

5. **Rig detail writ fetch:** When `showRigDetail(rig)` is called, writ data (`title` + `body`) needs to be fetched. The existing `GET /api/writ/show?id=...` route returns `WritDoc & { links: WritLinks }`. The links can be ignored; only `title` and `body` are needed.

6. **Template spec JSON in expanded view:** The brief says "the expanded view should also include the template spec json for review." This is the raw `RigTemplate` object formatted as JSON, shown below the graphical pipeline view. This is an exact dump of the registered template — not the config YAML, but the parsed/resolved object.

