## RigTemplateRegistry (spider.ts private class)

```
templates:           Map<string, RigTemplate>  — ALL templates, config + kit-qualified
configMappings:      Map<string, string>        — guild.json writ-type → template-name
kitMappings:         Map<string, string>        — kit writ-type → template-name
configTemplateNames: Set<string>               — unqualified names of config-declared templates
```

Config templates: stored under unqualified name (`"default"`).
Kit templates: stored under qualified name (`"pluginId.templateName"`).

Provenance: name in `configTemplateNames` → source is guild.json. Otherwise source is the plugin ID (the prefix before the first `.`).

Writ type mappings: `configMappings` and `kitMappings` together. To show which writ types map to a template, these need to be inverted (template name → [writ types]).

To expose this info externally, a new `listRigTemplates(): RigTemplateInfo[]` method is needed on SpiderApi.

