`RigDoc.writId` exists; `WritDoc.title` is needed. Options:

**Option A — frontend per-row fetch:** `GET /api/writ/show?id={writId}` per rig. Auto-route from `writ-show` tool (`clerk:read` permission). Max 100 rigs → 100 fetches. Workable but chatty.

**Option B — new backend enriched route:** `GET /api/spider/rigs` in `oculus-routes.ts` that fetches all rigs then batch-looks up writs via `stacks.readBook<WritDoc>('clerk', 'writs')`. Single fetch from frontend; requires `ClerkApi` import in `oculus-routes.ts`.

**Note:** The spider already imports `ClerkApi` and opens a writ read-book at startup. The oculus-routes.ts file currently only imports from `fabricator-apparatus` and `nexus-core`.

