## Current `/api/spider/config` Route

`packages/plugins/spider/src/oculus-routes.ts` — returns:
```json
{
  "rigTemplates": { /* ONLY guild.json-declared templates */ },
  "engineDesigns": [ { "id": "...", "pluginId": "...", "hasCollect": false } ],
  "blockTypes": [ { "id": "...", "pluginId": "...", "pollIntervalMs": 60000 } ]
}
```

**Critical gap:** `rigTemplates` comes from `guildConfig().spider.rigTemplates` — only config-declared templates. Kit-contributed templates (registered via `RigTemplateRegistry.registerFromKit()`) are completely absent. The registry lives in spider.ts's closure with no public getter.

---

## RigTemplateRegistry (spider.ts private class)

Internal state:
```
templates:           Map<string, RigTemplate>  — ALL templates, config + kit-qualified
configMappings:      Map<string, string>        — guild.json writ-type → template-name
kitMappings:         Map<string, string>        — kit writ-type → template-name
configTemplateNames: Set<string>               — unqualified names of config-declared templates
designSourceMap:     Map<string, string>        — designId → pluginId (internal, startup)
```

- Config templates: stored under unqualified name (e.g. `"default"`)
- Kit templates: stored under qualified name (e.g. `"myplugin.default"`)
- Provenance recovery: name in `configTemplateNames` → guild.json; otherwise plugin ID is prefix before first `.`
- Writ type mappings need inversion: template name → list of writ types

To expose this info, a new `listRigTemplates(): RigTemplateInfo[]` method needs to be added to SpiderApi.

---

## Auto-Generated REST Routes via Oculus

Auto-mapped tool routes (relevant):
- `GET /api/rig/list` — from `rig-list` tool
- `GET /api/rig/show?id=...` — from `rig-show` tool
- `GET /api/writ/show?id=...` — from `writ-show` tool (clerk, `clerk:read`)
- `GET /api/writ/list` — from `writ-list` tool
- `GET /api/session/show?id=...` — from `session-show` tool (animator, `read`)

Custom routes (take precedence over auto-routes if same path):
- `GET /api/spider/config` — from `oculus-routes.ts`

---

## Writ Title Data Path

`RigDoc.writId` exists; `WritDoc.title` is needed. Three options:

**Option A — frontend per-row fetch:** Call `GET /api/writ/show?id={writId}` for each row. Max 100 rigs. Workable but chatty.

**Option B — new backend enriched route:** `GET /api/spider/rigs` in `oculus-routes.ts` joins rigs + writ titles. Single frontend fetch. Requires adding `ClerkApi` import to `oculus-routes.ts` (which currently only uses `FabricatorApi` and `SpiderApi`).

**Option C — frontend bulk writ fetch:** `GET /api/writ/list` once, build id→title map. Pagination risk if > 20 writs.

---

## Session Log Data Path

**While running** (`engine.status === 'running'`, `engine.sessionId` set):
- `SessionDoc.status = 'running'`; no transcript in Stacks yet
- Animator writes full transcript only on completion — no incremental Stacks writes
- Only option: poll `GET /api/session/show?id=...` until terminal; show spinner

**After completion:**
- `SessionDoc.output` — final assistant text (clean, human-readable)
- `TranscriptDoc.messages` — full raw NDJSON array (no existing REST endpoint)

**SSE precedent:** Parlour uses `streamSSE` from `hono/streaming` in `packages/plugins/parlour/src/routes.ts`. Frontend reads SSE via manual `ReadableStream` parser in `packages/plugins/parlour/src/static/parlour/app.js`. This is the established codebase pattern for streaming.

**Practical recommendation:** A new `GET /api/spider/session-output?sessionId=...` route in `oculus-routes.ts` that reads `stacks.readBook<SessionDoc>('animator', 'sessions')`, returns `{ status, output }`. Frontend polls this every few seconds while `status === 'running'`, shows spinner, renders output text in resizable textarea once terminal.

---

## Elapsed Time Display

Data already on `EngineInstance`: `startedAt?: string`, `completedAt?: string`. No backend changes needed.

Brief scope: "for engines which have completed" — only show for `status === 'completed'`. Show placeholder while running. Format: `Xh Xm Xs` dropping leading zero units (e.g. `13m 22s`, not `0h 13m 22s`).

---

## Quick Engine Cost Display

Quick engine: `engine.sessionId !== undefined`. Cost data in `SessionDoc` from `GET /api/session/show?id={engine.sessionId}`. No new backend routes needed.

Fields: `tokenUsage.inputTokens`, `tokenUsage.outputTokens`, `costUsd`. Both may be `undefined` if provider doesn't report them. Show only when `engine.status === 'completed'`.

